<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Remote access (paired desktop) transmits cleartext ws:// to whatever host the
  user paired. Android's default NSC (API 28+) blocks cleartext to arbitrary
  hosts, which produced "Connection closed before auth" because the QR/pairing
  URL encodes a raw Tailscale CGNAT IP (e.g. 100.64.1.2) or a LAN IP — neither
  is a .ts.net MagicDNS domain, so the prior allowlist blocked every real
  pairing target.

  We permit cleartext broadly here. The app's threat model (documented in
  desktop/CLAUDE.md) assumes: (1) Tailscale users get WireGuard encryption
  end-to-end under the cleartext WS, (2) LAN users accept the same cleartext
  exposure the desktop-to-browser remote path already has, and (3) every
  connection is still gated by a bcrypt-verified password handshake at the
  WebSocket layer. User intent is explicit — they pair a device before
  connecting. If we ever ship WSS, tighten this back up.
-->
<network-security-config>
    <base-config cleartextTrafficPermitted="true" />
</network-security-config>
